programme.title: Great Games

programme.title: Great Games

programme.title: Great Games

programme.desc: Mount Kenya soars over 5km into the air. It is the second highest mountain in Africa. At its summit, temperatures fluctuate from over 30 degrees celsius to below freezing.
programme.sub-title: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ngorongoro: Born of Fire
programme.desc: Ngorongoro is thought to have formed about 2.5 million years ago from a large volcano, whose cone collapsed inward after a major eruption. This fertile land is full of wildlife, from cunning hyena and proud lions to vast herds of wildebeest and elephants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: The Christmas Gift
programme.desc: Inspired by a true story. Ten-year-old Wesley puts together a "Secret Santa" gift for a needy child and when ten-year-old Megan opens the package, she discovers an item that will have a huge impact on her life to come.

programme.title: All I Want For Christmas
programme.desc: One Christmas a boy wishes he could change places and his dream comes true! But he soon discovers that without his parents and friends it's actually a curse. The only problem is - can he reverse his disastrous wish and get his family back again.

programme.title: A Family for the Holidays
programme.desc: Becky and her family are always in a hurry and rarely have the time to speak with her sweet, elderly neighbor Grace who always trying to start conversation with her.

programme.title: One Bad Christmas
programme.desc: Big Earl is the owner of a Christmas tree lot, he has a big heart and big visions. The week before Christmas, his son Derrick, trying to prove to his dad that he is a success, gets into trouble and puts the survival of his dad’s business in jeopardy.

programme.title: Holiday Wishes
programme.desc: Britney, a rich, spoiled child, and Rachel, an orphan, switch bodies after a visit to the mall with Santa Claus. Each girl wakes up as the other - Britney is in the orphanage, and Rachel is at Britney's family's mansion.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: Twelve Trees Of Christmas
programme.desc: Starring Lindy Booth, Melanie Brown, and Robin Dunne. Cheri rallies her Manhattan neighborhood to participate in a Christmas tree contest when their local library is abruptly set for demolition by an ambitious but handsome developer. Feat: Mel B.

programme.title: Holiday Joy

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Manchurian Candidates

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Was Presidential hopeful, Robert F. Kennedy really killed by disgruntled Palestinian Sirhan Sirhan as we’ve been led to believe? Or was he another in a long line of Manchurian candidates, a victim of a long standing mind control program.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard witnesses a municipal employee in Toronto, Canada undergo a regression during which he re-experiences a previous life as a doctor in early 20 century England.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Does the Bible contain hidden messages encoded within certain passages of the Old Testament? Is the prophetic nature of these 'codes' proof the Bible's author is of supernatural or extraterrestrial origin?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard interviews the expedition organizer who is planning on leading a team of scientists, filmmakers and tourists to the Arctic aboard a Russian nuclear ice-breaker in search of an entrance into the interior of our world.
programme.sub-title: Journey to the Center of the Earth

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard meets members of the 9/11 Truth movement who challenge the official version of events concerning the attack on the U.S. Pentagon. Researchers present evidence to suggest the attack was perpetrated by some rogue element inside the U.S. government.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the supposed mastermind behind the 9/11 terrorist attacks and leader of the Al Qaeda terrorist cell remained a CIA asset until his death.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard speaks with two investigative journalists and a natural health practitioner who maintain vaccines are neither safe nor effective.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Can radiation from electrical appliances, power lines, microwave ovens, and wireless technology such as cell phones, baby monitors, alter our DNA, and cause illnesses?
programme.sub-title: The Dangers of EMF (Electro Magnetic Frequencies)

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Alien Abductions
programme.desc: Richard speaks with two alleged alien abductees about their claims they were taken aboard an alien space craft.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: For centuries, farmers have been discovering strange, complex geometric patterns comprised of rings, circles and other intricate shapes in their fields.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard meets the owners of an abnormal humanoid skull allegedly discovered in Mexico in the 1930s and a researcher who has had the skull subjected to numerous tests including carbon-14 dating, and DNA in order to determine it’s origin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Mystery of Oak Island
programme.desc: Richard investigates Canada's best-known mysteries, the Oak Island treasure. Also known as the money pit, the site has become one of the world's deepest and most costly archaeological digs.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Energy Healing
programme.desc: Several energy healers claim they are able to produce spontaneous miraculous healing through a laying on of hands. Claims of similar such healing by a man in a remote village in Brazil, known as John of God are also examined.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray
programme.desc: In this re-examination of the assassination of civil rights leader Martin Luther King, Richard meets several researchers who provide evidence that the convicted gunman, James Earl Ray was not the real triggerman.
programme.sub-title: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Birthers - Obama's Birth Certificate
programme.desc: Richard interviews several prominent 'Birthers' who present evidence that proves Barack Obama is not eligible to be President because he does not meet the qualifications of a natural born citizen.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: RFID Chips
programme.desc: Could implantable RFID chips or Radio-frequency identification tags currently in widespread use in retail industry be used to surreptitiously track and control people?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Assassination of John Lennon
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show travels to New York, LA and Toronto in order to investigate the murder of John Lennon. Several researchers posit that Lennon's supposed killer Mark David Chapman was either a patsy or a mind-controlled assassin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?
programme.desc: Is it conceivable that the Doors legendary front man did not die in a bathtub in Paris of an apparent drug overdose?
programme.sub-title: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Water Engine
programme.desc: Did the late Stanley Meyer figure out a way to run an internal combustion engine on pure water? And was he murdered because of the threat his invention posed to Big Oil?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Murder of Marilyn Monroe
programme.desc: Did this pop icon and blond bombshell succumb to a drug overdose in 1962 as we've been led to believe or was she killed for 'knowing too much?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the medical profession, drug companies, the food industry and government agencies are suppressing a cure for cancer.
programme.sub-title: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Bilderbergs
programme.desc: A glimpse backstage at the highly secretive annual gathering of the world's richest and most powerful movers and shakers.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Shroud of Turin
programme.desc: Is this famous piece of linen cloth the actual burial cloth of Jesus Christ or a clever Medieval hoax?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Fake Arab Spring?
programme.desc: Who was really behind a series of revolts, protests, and uprisings that swept the Middle East starting in late 2010?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Ouija Boards?
programme.desc: Harmless board game or portal to the spirit world? Richard delves into the history and folklore of 'talking boards' with a collector of Ouija boards and a world renowned paranormal investigator.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Global Warming, A Hoax?
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several journalists and researchers who argue the theory that human use of carbon-based fossil fuels will lead to catastrophic global warming.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: JFK
programme.desc: Richard meets with some prominent JFK assassination researchers to discuss the November 1963 murder of President John F. Kennedy.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Pterodactyls
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several explorers and cryptozoologists who believe pterodactyls, flying dinosaurs thought to have become extinct some 60 million years ago, are alive and thriving in remote places such as Papua New Guinea.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: GMO - Genetically Modified Food
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims crop plants created for human or animal consumption using the latest molecular biology techniques are unsafe.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Fluoride
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show investigates the safety and efficacy of putting fluoride in our water supply. Dentists say that putting fluoride in the water supply prevents tooth decay, but some researchers claim it's a toxic substance that causes cancer.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Area 51
programme.desc: What's going on inside Area 51, America's most carefully guarded secret? The mysterious military base located 30 minutes north west of Las Vegas has been rumored to be involved in back engineering advanced alien technology recovered from UFO crash sites.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Remote Viewing
programme.desc: We meet several individuals who claim they have the ability to transcend time and space and identify people, objects, and locations hidden from their view.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Kunsthistorisches Museum, Vienna

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the National Archeological Museum of Athens

programme.sub-title: Inside the National Archeological Museum of Athens

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Egyptian Museum

programme.desc: From a scientist who recreates the crucifixion to an ancient amulet that proves Star Trek's Spock is Jewish, discover the secrets inside the Israel Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the State Hermitage Museum
programme.desc: From ancient mummies who sport tattoos to re-examining who really killed Rasputin, discover the secrets inside the State Hermitage Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Smithsonian Institution, Washington DC

programme.sub-title: Inside the Smithsonian Institution, Washington DC

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Imperial War Museum, London
programme.desc: From Churchill risking his life in the Blitz to 21st Century soldiers who become invisible, discover the secrets inside the Imperial War Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Imperial War Museum, London

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Vatican
programme.desc: From Michelangelo’s Sistine Chapel frescoes to the fall of the Knights Templar, discover the secrets inside the Vatican Museums.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Topkapi Palace Museum, Istanbul
programme.desc: From assassins who plot to poison a Sultan to bitter enemies who sign the world’s first peace treaty, discover the secrets inside the Topkapi Palace Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Topkapi Palace Museum, Istanbul

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Chateau of Versailles, Paris
programme.desc: From the schemes of Marie Antoinette to the spectrum of a star that reveals the origin of human life, discover the secrets inside the Chateau of Versailles.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Chateau of Versailles, Paris

programme.title: Angry Planet: Defying Gravity
programme.desc: George experiences extremes of aviation and space training aboard Czech-built Albatross fighter jet, inside Zero-G plane, simulating zero gravity by diving 30,000 feet in giant parabolas and in spinning centrifuges producing 6 G's of force.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Boiling Lake
programme.desc: Tucked away, high in the mountains of the Caribbean island of Dominica lies a marvel of nature  a lake whose water literally boils and steams like a witch's cauldron.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Monsoon
programme.desc: In India's monsoon season George wades through waist-deep water in Bombay and leach-filled waterfalls in Goa, finds people being swept away by rivers, and rebuilding bridges. He experiences an intense annual Hindu celebration.

programme.title: Angry Planet: African Hellhole
programme.desc: George explores the deadly Nyiragongo volcano in the Congo jungle but the lava lake dwelling inside it's crater may be the least of his worries as he has to negotiate through armed conflict, a family of gorillas, and severe weather.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Hurricane
programme.desc: Linking up with legendary storm chaser Jim Leonard, George flies to Jamaica to track Hurricane Dean. George then travels to Nova Scotia to experience the even bigger turmoil of Hurricane Noel at the iconic Maritime village of Peggy's Cove.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Thunder Down Under
programme.desc: In Australia George teams up with storm chaser Jimmy Deguara to witness summer storms in the outback. While in Oz, he dives the magnificent Great Barrier Reef, and explores just how painful is the sting of the venomous Box Jellyfish.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Arctic Winter
programme.desc: George links up with two experienced polar adventurers to explore frigid Canadian Arctic winter. The team uses skis to cross the fractured sea ice of Frobisher Bay, then dog teams to head North through the spectacular Auyuittuq Mountains.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Fire And Water
programme.desc: It's the intense summer wildfires that often plague the area during their 24 hours of daylight. He travels by train, bike, plane and whitewater raft to reach the fires but Mother Nature has other plans for him and doesn't make things easy.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Avalanches
programme.desc: Whenever there is unstable snow and gravity, gravity always wins. George travels to the Rocky Mountains to learn about how to stay alive in the back country.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Hawaii: Surf & Snow
programme.desc: In Hawaii George explores the wild side: diving with Galapagos sharks, ascending to snow-covered Mauna Kea, dental cleaning by Peppermint Cleaner Shrimp, extreme surfing at Banzai Pipeline, getting his boots lit on fire by Kilauea volcano.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Hottest and Coldest
programme.desc: George meets ultra-marathon runners in searing heat of Death Valley and bone-chilling cold of the Yukon. He dog-sleds in snow and meets wild characters like Caveman Bill, who has lived alone in a cave through 12 long cold Yukon winters.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Empty Quarter
programme.desc: The Empty Quarter is a windswept area of sand dunes. In a tiny corner of this vast desert lies Dubai, a glitzy ultra-modern playground. George heads out from Abu Dhabi on a 4W safari to see both sides of this corner of Arabia.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Crystal Cave
programme.desc: In 2000 in Chihuahua, Mexico, miners found a cave filled with giant crystals. Temperatures reach 120 degrees F and humidity nearly 100%. George leads an Explorers Club Flag Expedition into this extreme environment.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Italia Wild
programme.desc: In Italy, George studies avalanches of Dolomite Mountains, meets engineers who keep Venice from sinking, and heads South to explore Italy's explosive volcanoes: Vesuvius, Etna and Stromboli.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Volcanic Wedding
programme.desc: Most people's idea of a dream wedding might include a horse drawn carriage and an elaborate ceremony. Not George. Join him as he and his bride to be tie the knot in an unusual and certainly exotic way.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Venezuela Lightning
programme.desc: Gas from Catatumbo swamps mixed with cold air from the Andes create a perpetual lightning storm on South America's largest lake. From here George canoes 84 km to world's highest waterfall, swims with piranhas and holds a huge Anaconda.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Elephant Cave
programme.desc: Waterfall-shrouded Kitum Cave has been carved out by elephants in search of salt on Mount Elgon at the Kenya-Uganda border. George gets bitten by one of the cave bats suspected of carrying the deadly Marburg virus.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Midwest Stormfest
programme.desc: This season the tornadoes begin early - in February. Through the season, George follows the big weather from Missouri west to the Dakotas, and dodges the huge, destructive Greensburg tornado in southern Kansas.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Indonesia
programme.desc: In Indonesia George visits massive Komodo Dragons, explores steaming sulfur vents of Papandayan, visits villagers whose town got swept away by Sidoarjo Mudflow, and tackles his toughest climb to date - the very active Semeru Volcano.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Tornadoes
programme.desc: George embarks on his annual pilgrimage to the "Tornado Alley" area of the central U.S. to guide groups of people who want to witness the brute force of tornadoes in action

programme.title: Naked Science: Saturn
programme.desc: Saturn is the second-largest planet in the solar system. Storms on this gas giant can cover an area bigger than the United States Clouds of the gas race around the planet at over 1000 miles per hour generating fierce electrical storms and lightning.

programme.title: Naked Science: Anatomy Of Tornado
programme.desc: Tornados are one of the most destructive forces of the planets with winds at 300 miles an hour. They can destroy buildings and hurl cars hundreds of feet through the air.

programme.title: Naked Science: Mars
programme.desc: Mars our closest neighbor now a lifeless planet – but it may once have had water and therefore life. Naked Science investigates the red planet to learn how it was formed, how it became barren, and ask whether it ever will be possible to colonize it?

programme.title: Naked Science: Great Lakes
programme.desc: The Great Lakes are sometimes referred to as inland seas; they are the largest freshwater system in the world. Naked Science examines the early history of these amazing bodies

programme.title: Naked Science: How To Destroy A Planet

programme.title: World's Greatest: Nearshore Islands
programme.desc: Some of the world’s greatest islands are so close that they blend in with the mainland. But regardless of their size and origins, they are often the islands we are drawn to the most, each forging their own unique identity.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: Hitler unveils his military plans: annex Austria, seize the Sudetenland, and eventually invade Poland and the Soviet Union. By March 1938, Austria falls bloodlessly. By September 1939, he invades Poland, sparking World War Two.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: Hitler rules Europe triumphantly, hailed as a hero in Germany. Hitler invades the Soviet Union, promising swift victory over communism, but progress stalls. As Germany faces setbacks, Hitler retreats to his bunker in Poland, increasingly reliant on drugs.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: This is the story of how Hitler orchestrated the genocide of 6 million Jews. Hitler portrayed Jews as a societal threat, using Goebbels' propaganda. Deportations were masked as resettlements while Auschwitz-Birkenau became a death factory.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: By 1944, Hitler's image as a victorious leader is crumbling. He faces a bomb plot led by Stauffenberg and Tresckow, intending to kill him and overthrow the regime. Hitler survives the bombing, triggering a brutal reprisal against conspirators.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: In January 1945, Nazi Germany faces defeat as Allied armies close in. Hitler, aged 55 and in poor health, remains defiant in his Berlin bunker. On April 30th, 1945, Hitler commits suicide, and days later, Germany surrenders, ending World War II.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: In WWII's final months, Allies discover Nazi death camps, prompting a sweeping denazification of Germany post-war. Nuremberg trials convict top Nazis. Former Nazis are employed by the West in the Cold War struggle against the Soviet Union.

programme.title: War Story: Where Hell is: The Leopold and the Scheldt
programme.desc: The Allies liberated Antwerp, the world’s largest deep-water port, on 4 September 1944, but it could only be accessed via the Scheldt Estuary, the perfect place for the Germans to make a stand.
programme.sub-title: Where Hell is: The Leopold and the Scheldt

programme.title: War Story: Falaise, the corridor of death
programme.desc: The Canadian army played the pivotal role in closing the Falaise Gap and ensuring Allied victory in the Normandy Campaign in August 1944.

programme.title: War Story: D-Day plus 1
programme.desc: The Canadian stand against the 12th SS Panzer Division Hitlerjugend immediately after D-Day allowed the Allies to switch to the offensive and truly begin the liberation of Europe.

programme.title: War Story: Surviving Dieppe
programme.desc: The Dieppe assault of 19 August 1942 is the worst day in Canadian military history: in just 8 hours, 907 Canadians were killed. For 2,000 of their comrades, nearly three years of incarceration in German prison camps followed.

programme.title: War Story: Whistle for a Tiffy
programme.desc: From D-Day, Tactical Air Force fighter-bombers played a pivotal role in Allied battlefield success; Canadian soldiers knew they could always “whistle for a Tiffy”.

programme.title: War Story: Behind Enemy Lines
programme.desc: Royal Canadian Air Force bombing operations play a crucial role in disrupting German infrastructure ahead of the Normandy invasion of June 1944. In the process, dozens of Canadian airmen are forced to bail out over occupied Belgium and France.

programme.title: War Story: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad
programme.desc: In the summer of 1942, the Germans advance to seize the rich oilfields of the Caucasus. In their path, the city of Stalingrad, its Soviet defenders personally ordered by Stalin to “take not one step back".
programme.sub-title: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad

programme.title: War Story: Buchenwald Airmen
programme.desc: For two months in 1944, 168 Allied airmen were shot down over occupied France, betrayed to the Gestapo by the same collaborator, transported to the Nazi concentration and slave labour camp Buchenwald.

programme.title: War Story: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt
programme.desc: On 16 April 1945, a mere three weeks before German surrender, the submarine fired a single torpedo that sank the last Canadian naval vessel lost to enemy action.
programme.sub-title: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt

programme.title: War Story: Prisoners of the Sun
programme.desc: On 16 November 1941, two Canadian battalions arrived in the British colony of Hong Kong. Their aim: Bolster the Empire’s defenses in the event of aggression by the restless forces of Japan, stationed only kilometres away in occupied China.

programme.title: War Story: Vengeance
programme.desc: In 1941, nearly 30,000 Jews escaped the ghettos and work camps and they joined the growing underground resistance army, actively fighting the Nazis.

programme.title: War Story: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany
programme.desc: In mid-September 1944, the remnants of the battered 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion participated in the largest parachute drop in history, fought a successful battle.
programme.sub-title: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany

programme.title: War Story: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy
programme.desc: In Normandy, the 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion proved itself to be in the vanguard of the best-trained and toughest units in the Allied forces.
programme.sub-title: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy

programme.title: War Story: The Road to Rome
programme.desc: The Road to Rome examines the incredible experiences of Canadian veterans, the victories and horrors of armoured combat, and the pivotal value, far too often neglected, of the overall Italian Campaign.

programme.title: War Story: Ortona: The War Inside
programme.desc: The War Inside is a personal retelling of one of the fiercest battles of the Italian Campaign from the searing points of view of Canadian infantrymen, a tanker, a stretcher bearer, and a German paratrooper.

programme.title: War Story: Sicily: The First Campaign
programme.desc: The Sicily Campaign began with the largest seaborne invasion in history on 9-10 July 1943. The Allied forces of Britain, Canada, and the United States sought to knock Italy out of the war and attack Germany from the south.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan continues its suicidal resistance, and invading it looks costly. After 2 atomic bombs, the Emperor intervenes and stops the War. Stalin grabs territory in East Asia. The War is over, and the Atomic Era and the Cold War start.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1945, Germany is crumbly on both fronts. The Western Allies cross the Rhine and take most of Germany, while the Red Army quickly advances into Berlin. After Hitler's suicide, Germany surrenders and is divided among the allied powers.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Marines succeed in the "island hopping" strategy against suicidal resistance. The US Navy establishes supremacy, cutting off Japan.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.desc: French's signature yellow mustard is the number-one selling mustard in America; turkey, duck, and chicken meat all stitched together in one giant dish,Turduckens by the thousands.

programme.title: Food Factory USA
programme.desc: Jack Link's South Dakota factory turns meat into beef jerky; mountains of raw sugar are cleaned and steamed into dainty Domino sugar cubes; this New Jersey factory makes brownies.

programme.title: Food Factory USA
programme.desc: Caramel and coconut combine to make Samoas, a popular brand of cookie from the Girl Scouts; creating Turkey Hill Double Decker ice-cream sandwiches; cheddar cheese is stuffed into SuperPretzel Softstix.

programme.title: Food Factory USA
programme.desc: Going behind the manufacturing process of Welch's Concord grape jam, Mrs. T's pierogies, and chocolate-covered pretzels.

programme.title: Food Factory USA
programme.desc: A Pennsylvania bakery makes 28 donuts per second; pepperoni rolls come out picture-perfect; a freshly popped multigrain snack that originated in Korea.

programme.title: Food Factory USA
programme.desc: Iconic cheesecakes on a stick, hand-dipped in chocolate; a monster wheel of cheddar; irresistible blondies sent across the country.

programme.title: Laila
programme.desc: Laila Paattinen is a working woman. Tired of low-paying jobs, she completed a five-month course in dry-wall installation. Because she had chosen a non-traditional job for women, she solved her problems by opening her own dry-wall application business.

programme.title: Boys Will Be Men
programme.desc: This film takes an inside look at the world of juvenile delinquency. We are shown the tough existence on the streets of Montréal, but it could be any city in North America. Some boys as young as ten years of age talk about their lives of crime.

programme.title: Worth Every Minute
programme.desc: A tribute to Pat Schulz, a working-class heroine known for her '50s human and workers' rights battles. This documentary offers a historical view of the women's movement, tracing its roots, early issues, current concerns, and emerging directions.

programme.title: To A Safer Place
programme.desc: To a Safer Place" follows Shirley Turcotte's journey as an incest survivor. Returning to her past, she confronts family violence with courage. Her story inspires survivors to find healing and dignity through frank disclosures.

programme.title: My Grandmother Ironed The Kings Shirts
programme.desc: Torill Kove's grandmother often told her stories. One in particular revolved around ironing shirts for the King of Norway. And what if that intriguing detail was just the tip of the iceberg?

programme.title: Unwanted Soldiers
programme.desc: Filmmaker Jari Osborne discovers her father's WWII involvement, revealing discrimination against Chinese-Canadians. His secret missions in Southeast Asia shed light on their quiet heroism, paying moving tribute in this multi-layered documentary.

programme.title: Hands Of History
programme.desc: In this acclaimed 1994 documentary, Loretta Todd, a leading figure in Indigenous cinema in Canada, profiles four contemporary female artists.The film is a moving testimony to the vital role Indigenous women play in nurturing Indigenous cultures.

programme.title: A Mother And Daughter On Abortion
programme.desc: The document of an intimate conversation between a mother and her adult daughter. They speak candidly about their personal experiences in trying to obtain an abortion, and how, in different decade, each got caught up in the system and its rules.

programme.title: Listening For Something Adrienne Rich And Dionne Brand In Conversation
programme.desc: The nation, the country, where do we belong in it? In this film through conversation and poetry two poets meet for the telling and the listening. Topics include political issues, feminism, racism and lesbianism, among others.

programme.title: Waiting For Fidel
programme.desc: Three Canadians, including ex-premier Joseph Smallwood and NFB director Michael Rubbo, travel to Cuba, aiming to cast Fidel Castro. Their journey offers insights into Cuba's changes and their own views.

programme.title: Gurdeep Singh Bains
programme.desc: Gurdeep is a thirteen-year-old Canadian Sikh whose family runs a dairy farm near Chilliwack, British Columbia. They have retained their language and religion. Sometimes he feels a little different from the other children because he wears a turban.

programme.title: Sunrise Over Tiananmen Square
programme.desc: Shui-Bo Wang's animated documentary intertwines personal journey with history, exploring China's '60s-'80s upheavals. From symbol of hope to tragedy, it depicts Wang's roles from Red Guard to teacher, exploring idealism and intolerance.

programme.title: Toward Intimacy
programme.desc: Toward Intimacy" celebrates the rights of women with disabilities to pursue intimate relationships. This one-hour film features personal stories from four Canadian women, addressing sexuality, self-esteem, stereotypes, and parenting.

programme.title: The Glass Ceiling
programme.desc: Whether in the public service or on the shop floor, discrimination against women is taking on increasingly subtle forms, which makes it even more difficult to eliminate.

programme.title: Challenger An Industrial Romance
programme.desc: Follows the development of Canadair's super-executive jet. The film captures the spirit of the Canadian air transport industry and its attempt to compete with the American leaders in the industry.

programme.title: Spirit Of The Kata
programme.desc: Five women, all of them black belts in karate, are examples of how this ancient martial art can transform lives. They demonstrate how it can generate a whole range of physical, psychological and spiritual benefits.

programme.title: First Stories - Two Spirited
programme.desc: This short documentary presents the empowering story of Rodney "Geeyo" Poucette's struggle against prejudice in the Indigenous community as a two spirited person (gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender).

programme.title: If You Love This Planet
programme.desc: This film records a lecture given to students by outspoken nuclear critic, Dr. Helen Caldicott, president of Physicians for Social Responsibility in the United States. Her message is clear: disarmament cannot be postponed.

programme.title: Kathleen Shannon On Film Feminism Other Dreams
programme.desc: With intelligence and humour, documentary filmmaker, Kathleen Shannon speaks her formative years at the National Film Board, and the gradual awakening of an unshakeable determination to give women filmmakers a chance to tell their stories of the world

programme.title: Chaque Enfant
programme.desc: This is the story of a baby who appears mysteriously on the doorstep of a busy executive, and who is subsequently bounced from household to household down the block. Nobody in the community is interested in caring for the baby without a name.

programme.title: Horse Drawn Magic
programme.desc: The Caravan Stage Company is the only horse-drawn open-air theatre in the world. Every summer it tours British Columbia and Alberta, bringing live entertainment to communities where television is often the main diversion.

programme.title: The Impossible Takes A Little Longer
programme.desc: Documents the work and personal lives of five physically disabled women. It shows how they are coping with the problems they share with all women, the problems they share with other disabled women and those unique to their particular circumstances.

programme.title: Holy Angels
programme.desc: Jay Cardinal Villeneuve’s short documentary Holy Angels powerfully recaptures Canada’s colonialist history through impressionistic images and the fragmented language of a child.

programme.title: Julie Obrien
programme.desc: This film is loosely structured around Julie O'Brien, eleven’s school assignment to write an essay about the old times in Newfoundland, how they have changed, how they are still remembered.

programme.title: Twenty Years Of Feminist Filmmaking
programme.desc: A clip montage for presentation at the National Action Committee on the Status of Women to commemorate the 20th anniversary of Studio D and the National Action Committee.

programme.title: Waiting
programme.desc: The patient Dinkas of South Sudan endure famine amid civil strife. Aid arrives in Alek, but distribution is delayed to prevent unrest, revealing the stark reality of hunger.

programme.title: Children Of War
programme.desc: A remarkable documentary in which teenagers from war-torn countries, filmed in interaction with Canadian high-school students, speak with dignity, maturity and candor about the struggles of their people and the suffering they have endured.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane

programme.title: Das perfekte Weihnachten

programme.title: Weihnachtswunderland

programme.title: Unsere Lehrerin die Weihnachtshexe

programme.desc: MTV Unplugged' ist der Ritterschlag für die Größten der Großen; die 'Hall of Fame' des Musikfernsehens sozusagen. Nur den Besten wird die Möglichkeit geboten, ihre Songs live, akustisch, echt, ungeschönt und ungefiltert darzubieten.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: Max Raabe
programme.desc: Im legendären Clärchens Ballhaus, Berlin nahmen Max Raabe & Palast Orchester ihr MTV Unplugged auf. Im intimen Ambiente lud er sich dazu großartige Gäste ein: Lars Eidinger, Samy Deluxe, Pawel Popolski, Lea, Mr. Lordi, Namika und Herbert Grönemeyer.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Musikalische Reise ohne Grenzen
programme.desc: Zum ersten Mal ist 'Lieder, Land & Leute' in gleich drei Ländern zu Gast und präsentiert wunderschöne Bilder und Musik aus Kärnten, Slowenien und Südtirol.

programme.title: Stars auf hoher See: Unterwegs im Mittelmeer
programme.desc: Schlager Ahoi! GoldStar TV sticht auf der imposanten MSC Magnifica in See. Matthias Reim, Claudia Jung, Anita und Alexandra Hofmann, Andrea Rischka, René Ulbrich und viele mehr präsentieren ihren größten Hits.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Passeiertal
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer begibt sich in das Passeiertal in Südtirol. Es erstreckt sich auf einer Länge von ca. 50 km von Meran bis zum Timmelsjoch. Dagmar präsentiert mit ihren Gästen die schönsten Regionen Südtirols und verliebt sich in die Südtiroler Küche.

programme.title: Stars auf hoher See: Von der Adria bis zum Bosporus Teil 1
programme.desc: Frederic Meisner und Sonja Weissensteiner erkunden auf dem Luxusschiff "Costa Mediterranea" die schönsten Orte von der Adria bis zum Bosporus. Als besondere Gäste sind Stars wie Roberto Blanco, Michelle, Ireen Sheer und Matthias Reim mit an Bord.
programme.sub-title: Von der Adria bis zum Bosporus Teil 1

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Rund um den Kalterer See
programme.desc: Auch diesmal begrüßt Dagmar Obernosterer die Stars der Volksmusik. Marc Pircher, Mara Kayser, das Nockalm Quintett u.v.a. entführen Sie in die schönsten Regionen der Alpen. Die einmalige Landschaft rund um den Kalterer See macht Lust auf Südtirols Süden.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Sonnenparadies Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer ist zu Gast bei Freunden. Die Original Fidelen Lavanttaler, Marc Pircher u.v.a. begeistern das Fernsehpublikum. Ob am Wörthersee, am Großglockner oder im Nationalpark Hohe Tauern - das ist Natur, die beeindruckende Geschichten erzählt.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Winter aus Sterzing
programme.desc: Unsere musikalische Reise führt uns nach Sterzing in Südtirol. Moderatorin Dagmar Obernosterer begrüßt in dem malerischen Ort Interpreten wie Die jungen Zillertaler, Bergfeuer und Oswald Sattler.

programme.title: Schlagergala 2007: Teil 2
programme.desc: Wieder einmal gibt es Musik vom Feinsten aus Dorf Münsterland. Das Beste Konzert des deutschen Schlagers! Stars wie Fantasy, Kristina Bach, G.G. Anderson, Claudia Jung und DJ Ötzi zusammen mit Nik P. begeistern auf der Bühne.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Osttirol und Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer erkundet den Drauradweg von Osttirol nach Kärnten. Die Stars der Volksmusik singen dabei ihre Hits vor der einzigartigen Bergkulisse der Lienzer Dolomiten. Ob Kurt Elsasser, Alexandra Lexer u.v.a. den Drauradweg zum Schwingen bringen.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Osttirol und Kärnten

programme.title: Goldies: Folge 3
programme.desc: So schön kann doch kein Mann sein / Hell wie ein Diamant / Oh wann kommst du / Arizona Man / Ich bin verliebt in die Liebe / Die Sonne und du

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Gamlitz an der Südsteirischen Weinstraße
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer besucht die Region rund um Gamlitz an der südsteirischen Weinstraße. Sie begrüßt Oswald Sattler, die Stoakogler, Gilbert u.v.a. Auch Harmonikaweltmeister Primosch Zvir gibt eine Kostprobe seines Könnens.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Gamlitz an der Südsteirischen Weinstraße

programme.title: Andreas Fulterer - Mein Weg
programme.desc: Andreas Fulterer ist seiner Heimat Südtirol immer treu geblieben. Im Musikspecial "Mein Weg" zeigt er uns die schönsten Plätze und ist zudem mit seinen größten Hits in Konzertausschnitten zu sehen. Ein wunderschöner, besinnlicher Musikfilm.

programme.title: Schlagergala 2006: Teil 1
programme.desc: Das "Who Is Who" der deutschen Schlagerszene gibt sich ein Stelldichein und GoldStar TV ist live dabei! Stars wie Nino de Angelo, Mary Roos, Johnny Logan, Kristina Bach, Jürgen Drews und Karel Gott präsentieren ihre Hits im westfälischen Legenden.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in der Wachau und Bruck an der Mur
programme.desc: Viele Stars der Volksmusik begleiten Dagmar Obernosterer durch die malerische Hügellandschaft der Wachau. Petra Frey, Oswald Sattler, Simone u.v.a. verwöhnen Sie auf der Reise von Dürnstein über Bruck a. d. Mur bis nach Gamlitz mit ihren Liedern.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in der Wachau und Bruck an der Mur

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten
programme.desc: Eine herrliche Bergkulisse und traumhafter Pistenspaß - die Grubertaler und Marc Pircher bringen eine ordentliche Portion Hüttenzauber in Ihr Wohnzimmer. Hochkarätige Interpreten wie Mara Kayser, Oswald Sattler & Doris Russo sind ebenfalls mit dabei..
programme.sub-title: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten

programme.title: Um Amor Inesperado
programme.desc: É Natal e Sammi está buscando um pouco de sossego. Viciado em trabalho, Seth vem da cidade grande para explorar um terreno que recebeu de herança e que ele pretende vender antes do final do ano. A tranquilidade de Sammi é interrompida pela chegada de Seth

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: Uma Esperança de Natal
programme.desc: Sem ter onde morar, Rose, uma mãe solteira, e sua filha Katy redescobrem a esperança ao chegarem a um restaurante em uma pequena cidade.

programme.title: Festividades do Chocolate Quente
programme.desc: Colette dirige uma cafetaria conhecida pelo seu chocolate quente secreto e famoso. Marcus, um novo dono de sobremesa, começa a atrair os clientes da Colette, ela está determinada a expô-lo.

programme.title: Sobrevivendo Às Festas com Parentes
programme.desc: As irmãs Miranda e Lyla se reúnem para o Natal com suas famílias. Ao longo de três dias, alegria e caos causam estragos nos planos de férias das famílias e as antigas rivalidades entre irmãos surgem para sabotar a esperança diversão de fim de ano.

programme.title: Um Natal Encantado
programme.desc: Hugo, de doze anos, ainda acredita em elfos, mas é provocado por seus colegas, então decide se forçar a crescer. Mas quando sua família sai de férias de Natal, ele descobre que elfos moram no hotel.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Só Pode Ser Amor
programme.desc: Durante a temporada de Natal, três irmãs terão que decidir o que fazer com sua vida romântica quando partem para encontrar a família para as festas e seus respectivos pares surgem na cidade para tentar uma segunda chance.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Una Esperanza de Navidad
programme.desc: Esta es una encantadora y conmovedora historia navideña sobre la esperanza, el perdón y la fe, que cuenta cómo una madre soltera y su única hija de siete años encuentran un Santa Claus que puede cambiar sus vidas.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Una Esperanza de Navidad
programme.desc: Esta es una encantadora y conmovedora historia navideña sobre la esperanza, el perdón y la fe, que cuenta cómo una madre soltera y su única hija de siete años encuentran un Santa Claus que puede cambiar sus vidas.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Una Esperanza de Navidad
programme.desc: Esta es una encantadora y conmovedora historia navideña sobre la esperanza, el perdón y la fe, que cuenta cómo una madre soltera y su única hija de siete años encuentran un Santa Claus que puede cambiar sus vidas.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: Kanadas Küstenwölfe

programme.title: Vietnam
programme.desc: Im vietnamesischen Dorf Vinh Son lebt ein Großteil der Einwohner von der Schlangenzucht: Kobras, Gebänderte Rattenschlangen und sogar die extrem großen und giftigen Königskobras werden hier gehalten und verkauft - zumeist an den Nachbarn China. Der Vorsitzende des örtlichen Zuchtverbandes Kim Van Hoc war einer der ersten, der das lukrative Geschäft noch zu kommunistischen Zeiten entwickelte.

programme.title: Insekten
programme.desc: In der Natur gehören Insekten seit jeher auf den Speiseplan. Nur der Mensch macht vielerorts lange einen Bogen um sie. Heute ernähren sich bereits zwei Milliarden Menschen von den kleinen Krabbeltieren, vornehmlich in Afrika und Asien. Und langsam kommt auch Europa auf den Geschmack.

programme.title: Jenny und ihre Flughunde
programme.desc: Die Nordostküste Australiens ist die biologisch artenreichste Region des gesamten Kontinents. Sie ist auch die Heimat der Flughunde, die einst zu Hunderttausenden den 400 Kilometer langen Küstenstreifen bevölkerten. Doch die Populationen sind dramatisch gesunken - auch weil Obstfarmer die gefräßigen Fledertiere mit allen Mitteln bekämpft haben. In den letzten Jahren ist eine neue Gefahr für die Flughunde hinzugekommen: Eine mysteriöse Krankheit, die viele Tiere im Herbst befällt und sie von den Bäumen zu Boden stürzen lässt, wo sie qualvoll verenden. Jenny Maclean hat ihr Zuhause in ein Flughund-Hospital umgebaut, in dem sie Hunderte der possierlichen Tiere gesund pflegt. Planet Weltweit hat sie und ihre kleinen Patienten besucht.

programme.title: Schottland: Kampf, Clan und Königin
programme.desc: Schottlands bergiger Norden ist nicht nur der Sommersitz der Queen sondern auch Austragungsort der jährlichen Highland Games. Zum Finale in Braemar kommt die britische Königin als Schirmherrin persönlich. Die Spiele sind Bestandteil der Treffen schottischer Clans. Bei den sogenannten Gatherings kommen die Mitglieder, die inzwischen weltweit verstreut leben, einmal im Jahr zusammen. Planet Weltweit hat Captain Alwyn Farquharson, den Chief des Farquharson Clans, zu den Spielen und zum Gathering auf sein ehemaliges Schloss Invercauld begleitet.

programme.title: Der Andenkondor, König der Lüfte
programme.desc: Der Andenkondor, König der Lüfte? Ein Film von Christian HollerMit drei Meter Flügelspanne ist der Anden-Kondor der größte flugfähige Vogel Südamerikas - und einer der elegantesten der Welt. Mehrere Hunderte Kilometer kann er am Tag zurücklegen, wobei er die Aufwinde im südamerikanischen Andengebirge geschickt nutzt, um Energie zu sparen. In den letzten Jahren hat sich seine Heimat dramatisch verändert, was den Kondor immer weiter zurückdrängt. Der Ornithologe Lorenzo Sympson und der Paraglider Martin Vallmitjana wollen gemeinsam die Flug- und Lebensweise der Vögel erforschen und so nach einer Überlebenschance für die Tiere zu suchen. Planet Weltweit hat sie dabei beobachtet.

programme.title: Lappland, Rushhour im hohen Norden
programme.desc: Rund um Arjeplog, einem Ort in Schwedisch-Lappland mit 1.800 Einwohnern, liegt das Land der Sami. Seit Jahrtausenden lebt das auch als Lappen bezeichnete Volk von der Rentierzucht. Einige von ihnen haben es geschafft, diese alte Tradition bis heute zu bewahren. Die Rentierherden sind seit dem Frühjahr von der Küste immer höher in die Berge gezogen. Hier bringen die nordischen Hirsche ihre Kälber zur Welt. Im Herbst werden die Tiere zusammengetrieben und die Jungtiere markiert. Planet Weltweit begleitet den Zug der Rentiere vom Herbst bis in den Winter. Wie gelingt es den Lappen, in einer Welt zwischen Tradition und Moderne ihre naturnahe Lebensweise zu bewahren?

programme.title: Island
programme.desc: Im Frühjahr 2010 legte der isländische Vulkan Eyjafjallajökull halb Europa lahm, als seine Aschewolken über Tage den Flugverkehr behinderten. Auf Island selbst war vor allem die Region um das Dorf Vik an der äußersten Südspitze der Insel betroffen. Beim Ausbruch des Eyjafjallajökull ist Vik - außer der überall sichtbaren Asche - noch glimpflich davon gekommen. Doch was passiert, wenn auch der wesentlich größere Nachbarvulkan Katla ausbricht, dessen Kegel von einem riesigen Gletscher bedeckt ist? Ein Szenario, das in Islands Geschichte schon mehrmals vorkam. Planet Weltweit hat die Bewohner der Insel in ihrem Alltag zwischen Normalität und Katastrophenvorbereitung beobachtet.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Paris, Blitz Motorcycles
programme.desc: Fred Jourden und Hugo Jezegabel haben ihre Leidenschaft zum Beruf und zum Geschäft gemacht: In ihrer Werkstatt mitten in Paris fertigen sie kunstvoll aus alten Motorrädern neue, ganz besondere Zweiräder. Jedes Exemplar ist ein Unikat.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Japaner Kikuo Morimoto fördert in Kambodscha die traditionelle Webkunst und verschafft mit der Anpflanzung von Maulbeerbäumen und der Herstellung hochwertiger Seidenstoffe Hunderten von Menschen ein Einkommen. Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Big Bugs
programme.desc: Von der Massenwanderung der Monarchfalter zu den Turnieren der Hirschkäfer – dieser Film zeigt die spektakulärsten Wesen auf mehr als vier Beinen und ihre kuriosen Lebensgewohnheiten. Sie gehören zu den erfolgreichsten Tieren auf unserem Planeten - 80 Prozent aller bekannten Arten sind Gliederfüßer. Unter ihnen sind die größten Sonderlinge der Natur: Spinnen, die unter Falltüren lauern, Schmetterlinge, die Kontinente überqueren, Käfer, die einander vom Baum werfen oder gewiefte Konstrukteure von Treibsand-Fallen. Extreme Zeitlupenaufnahmen und innovative Makro-Kameratechniken erlauben neue Einblicke in das Leben der kleinen Wundertiere.

programme.title: Salif Keita, Souleymane Dournbia, Lansine Kouyate & N'Doumbé
programme.desc: Salif Keita's music is a rich combination of traditional Malian music with European and American influences. We can hear this in the instrumentation of Keita's music, which varies from traditional West-African instruments to Western European ones. The Malian singer was cast out by his family because of his albinism. In 1967 he moved to Bamako, where he started his musical career and joined Les Ambassadeurs (Internationaux). He achieved international acknowledgement with this band in the 1970s. After spending a couple of years in Ivory Coast, Salif has found his home base in Paris since 1984. During this 2010 concert, he proves to be rightfully referred to as “The Golden Voice of Africa”.

programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Jimmy Witherspoon & Rozaa Wortham
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. Jimmy Witherspoon and Rozaa Wortham, two incredible brilliant jazz musicians. Rozaa Wortham starts off the show with the Jimmy Witherspoon Quartet. Swinging and full of energy she performs ‘It Don't Mean A Thing'. Jimmy Witherspoon, known for the song “Ain't Nobody's Business” ends the show with some astounding lean-back blues.

programme.title: Kenny Barron
programme.desc: Pianist Kenny Barron's June 27, 2019 appearance at the Alfa Jazz Festival in Ukraine's Lviv was a celebration of sublime jazz virtuosity. The revered elder statesmen of jazz piano brought his regular working trio of Kiyoshi Kitagawa (bass) and Jonathan Blake (drums), augmented by stellar jazzman Marcus Strickland (tenor saxophone) and young lion Riley Mulherkar (trumpet). Their seamless blend of classic bebop and modern explorations spoke of a deep, emotive connection to each note, captivating the Ukrainian audience with lyrical improvisations during this unforgettable concert.

programme.title: John Coltrane, McCoy Tyner, Elvin Jones & Jimmy Garrison
programme.desc: The mere mention of the name John Coltrane evokes a deeply emotional, often spiritual response from even the most casual jazz fan. Dexter Gordon was a fantastic saxophonist. Miles Davis was a genius. Coltrane stood above - he was a visionary, a saint-like figure. By the standards of most jazz musicians, his life was uneventful. Sure, he had a heroin habit for a while, and Miles Davis punched him, but once he'd experienced the “spiritual awakening” described in the liner notes of his 1965 album A Love Supreme, he dedicated himself to his music with extreme single-mindedness. This broadcast of Coltrane's 1965 performance at the short-lived Belgian jazz festival in Comblain-la-Tour features Trane's classic quartet with Elvin Jones (drums), Jimmy Garrison (bass) and McCoy Tyner (piano).

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, West Of The West
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Omar Sosa, Childo Tomas, Ernesto Simpson & Leandro Saint-Hill
programme.desc: While always keeping one foot firmly anchored in the traditions of his home country, Cuba, Omar Sosa tirelessly explores music from the Caribbean to India, and West Africa to the Arab world. Since he left Cuba in 1993, the pianist has been blending his Afro-Cuban roots with jazz, hip hop, electro and world music. For his 2018 performance at Théâtre de Villefranche-sur-Saône, he brings to stage his Quarteto Afrocubano members Childo Tomas (electric bass & vocals), Ernesto Simpson (drums), and Leandro Saint-Hill (saxophones, flute, percussion & vocals). Together, they create a riveting instrumental dialogue. Celebrating rhythm in all its forms, this Omar Sosa concert is an intense and mystical experience.

programme.title: Freddie Hubbard, Al Grey, Alvin Batiste & Al Casey
programme.sub-title: Freddie Hubbard & The Satchmo Legacy Live in 1987
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. This concert of Freddie Hubbard and the Satchmo Legacy in 1987, highlights the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. Hubbard is an American jazz trumpeter whose unmistakable and influential tone contributed to new perspectives for modern jazz and bebop. He was also a well-known part of Art Blakey and the Jazz Messengers and is primarily known for playing bebop, hard bop, and post-bop styles from the early '60s onwards.

programme.title: Popa Chubby
programme.sub-title: Popa Chubby - It's A Mighty Hard Road
programme.desc: Popa Chubby, born as Ted Horowitz, is an American blues singer and guitarist, who has become one of the most popular figures of New York's blues scene. Early on in his career he released the album 'Booty and the Beast' (1995), which became one of the 1990s's best-selling blues albums. Chubby describes his own style as "The Stooges meets Buddy Guy, Motörhead meets Muddy Waters, and Jimi Hendrix meets Robert Johnson". As part of the French music festival Blues sur Seine, Chubby and his band played a great blues rock concert, showcasing the artist's powerful and soulful guitar playing. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Simone Signoret on November 8, 2019.

programme.title: Genesis
programme.desc: An English rock band formed at Charterhouse School, Godalming, Surrey in 1967. The band underwent many changes in musical style over its career, from folk music to progressive rock in the 1970s, before moving towards pop at the end of the decade. They have sold 21.5 million RIAA-certified albums in the US and their worldwide sales are estimated to be between 100 million and 150 million. Featuring archive material, music videos and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard)

programme.title: Gotthold Schwarz, Thomanerchor Leipzig, Gewandhausorchester Leipzig & Dorothee Mields
programme.sub-title: J. S. Bach – Christmas Oratorio, BWV 248
programme.desc: Traditionally, many ensembles festively announce the Christmas season with a performance of Johannes Sebastian Bach's Christmas Oratorio, BWV 248. It consists of six cantatas originally intended for performance on one of the major feast days of the Christmas period. The work saw its first performance in 1734, at St. Thomas Church in Leipzig, Germany, where Bach occupied the position of cantor. In that very same church the thirty-fourth ‘Thomaskantor', Gotthold Schwarz, leads the St. Thomas Boys Choir Leipzig and the Gewandhausorchester Leipzig in a performance of Bach's choral masterpiece. Among the soloists are Dorothee Mields (soprano), Elvira Bill (alto), Patrick Grahl (tenor, Evangelist), Markus Schäfer (tenor, arias), and Klaus Häger (bass). This performance was recorded in 2018.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances play Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's Violin Concerto No. 5 in A major, K. 219, also known as the ‘Turkish Concerto'. Leading violinist Grimal features as the soloist. With the exception of the first violin concerto, Mozart composed his other four violin concertos in 1775 at a time when he was concertmaster at the Salzburg court. It is the third and final movement that gives Concerto No. 5 its nickname, the ‘Turkish Concerto'. This movement features a striking middle section of ‘Turkish music', which the composer achieves not only by changing the meter, and the mode to minor, but also by letting the cellos and basses play col legno - creating a percussive sound with the wood of their bow. This performance was recorded at Cité de la Musique, France, in 2014.
